column1: Filename: Jornada_287001_npp_perennial_plant_phenology_data.csv     Last updated: 02/22/2018  By: Ken Ramsey
Dataset: Plant phenology transect at NPP sites
Project: Perennial Plant Phenology on NPP Sites
Study #:  287
Variable Information:
DATE              = date of observation [DD/MM/YYYY]
DOY               = day of year
ZONE              = vegetation zone  [C=Creosote G=Grassland M=Mesquite  P=Playa T=Tarbush]
SITE              = site name
SPP               = Species Code [4 letter acronym; see LTER site species list]
DORMANT           = Count (number of dormant individuals)
qf_dormant        = quality flag for DORMANT (blank=good  E=estimated  M=missing  Q=questionable)
NON-REP           = Count (number of non-reproductive individuals)
qf_nonrep         = quality flag for NONREP (blank=good  E=estimated  M=missing  Q=questionable)
BUD               = Count (number of individuals in bud)
qf_bud            = quality flag for BUD (blank=good  E=estimated  M=missing  Q=questionable)
FLOWER            = Count (number of individuals in flower)
qf_flower         = quality flag for FLOWER (blank=good  E=estimated  M=missing  Q=questionable)
FRUIT             = Count (number of individuals in fruit. Does not include OLD_FRUIT)
qf_fruit          = quality flag for FRUIT (blank=good  E=estimated  M=missing  Q=questionable)
TOTAL-OLD-FRUIT   = Count (number of individuals with old fruit = old-fruit-dormant plus old-fruit-nonrep)
OLD-FRUIT-DORMANT = Count (number of DORMANT individuals with old fruit)
OLD-FRUIT-NONREP  = Count (number of NON-REP individuals with old fruit)
METHOD            = Method used (B=belt transect; L=line transect)
SEEDLING          = seedling count
qf_seedling       = quality flag for SEEDLING (blank=good  E=estimated  M=missing  Q=questionable)
OBSERVER          = initials of field observer
TOTALOBS          = total of plants observed (dormant+non-rep+bud+flower+fruit)
PercentDORMANT    = percent of all phenophase observations that are Dormant (= Dormant count divided by count sum of all phenophases but discounting Old-Fruit)
PercentNON-REP    = percent of all phenophase observations that are Non-reproductive (= Dormant count divided by count sum of all phenophases but discounting Old-Fruit)
PercentBUD        = percent of all phenophase observations that are Bud (= Bud count divided by count sum of all phenophases but discounting Old-Fruit)
PercentFLOWER     = percent of all phenophase observations that are Flower (= Dormant count divided by count sum of all phenophases but discounting Old-Fruit)
PercentFRUIT      = percent of all phenophase observations that are Fruit (= Dormant count divided by count sum of all phenophases but discounting Old-Fruit)
COMMENT           = Comment section
